did.abstract: A collection of ephemeral publications issued by or referring to the microelectronics industry of California's "Silicon Valley." Includes promotional material, price lists, conference proceedings, newsletters, etc.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: An artificial collection of ephemeral publications issued by or referring to the microelectronics industry of California's "Silicon Valley." Includes promotional material, price lists, conference proceedings, newsletters, etc.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: An artificial collection kept by the library; multiple donors.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Silicon Valley Ephemera Collection. M0443. Dept. of Special Collections, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.

userestrict.head: Publication Rights
userestrict.p: Property rights reside with the repository. Literary rights reside with the creators of the documents or their heirs. To obtain permission to publish or reproduce, please contact the Public Services Librarian of the Dept. of Special Collections.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for research; materials must be requested at least 24 hours in advance of intended use. The Media materials require at least two weeks advance notice to use in order to allow staff time to have use copies made from the original items.
